# Backend Architecture Rules

Use DDD anemic + lightweight hexagonal architecture inside a modular NestJS monolith.

Each business module should follow this structure:

```txt
src/modules/{module}/
  domain/
    entities/
    enums/
    repositories/
    ports/
  application/
    use-cases/
    services/
  infrastructure/
    prisma/
    providers/
    mappers/
    openai/
  presentation/
    controllers/
    dto/
    guards/
```

Layer direction:

```txt
presentation -> application -> domain ports/repositories -> infrastructure adapters
```

Rules:
- Controllers must be thin.
- Controllers call use cases only.
- Business logic lives in application use cases or application services.
- Domain contains entities, enums, ports and repository contracts.
- Infrastructure contains Prisma, OpenAI and external provider implementations.
- Do not inject PrismaService directly into controllers.
- Do not call OpenAI directly from controllers or use cases.
- Use explicit use case names.
- Prefer small files and clear names.
- Avoid overengineering before the MVP is validated.
